<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n12134b"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n12" href="#n12134b">N12 (VI.B.14)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n12all.htm#n12134b"> 134(b)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> ~ price of pair of clogs</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Par hasard, quand j&apos;ai baptis&eacute; tant de milliers d&apos;hommes, ai-je attendu de quelqu&apos;un d&apos;entre eux m&ecirc;me la moiti&eacute; d&apos;un <i>scripulum</i>? Dites-moi et je vous le rendrai. Et quand le Seigneur a ordonn&eacute; quelque part des clercs par ma m&eacute;diocrit&eacute; et mon minist&egrave;re, je leur ai donn&eacute; gratuitement; et si j&apos;ai demand&eacute; &agrave; quelqu&apos;un d&apos;entre eux m&ecirc;me <mark>le prix de ma chaussure</mark>, reprochez-le-moi et je vous rendrai davantage. <br><font color="green">[When I baptised so many thousand men did I perchance ever expect from any one of them as much as half a <i>scripulum</i>? Tell me and I will give it to you. Or when the Lord ordained anywhere clergy through my humble ministry, I dispensed it gratuitously; and if I ever asked any one of them for even the cost of my footwear, reproach me with it and I will give you more.]</font> <small> Georges Dottin, <a name="GDSP" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#GDSP"><cite title="source">Les livres de Saint Patrick, ap&ocirc;tre de l'Irlande</cite></a> (n.d) 42/50</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
